<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="723" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="15.[1368,2574,290,956]" pageId="15" pageNumber="723">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1368,1606,526,559]" pageId="15" pageNumber="723">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The Asian Red-cheeked Squirrel is diurnal. It is partially terrestrial but also spends time high in canopy where it nests in tree hollows. It is found most often in dense shrub layer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
